  "targetAbstract": {
    "paragraphIndex": 4,
    "text": "Abstract. The history of design can be read as a sequence of changing answers to a deceptively simple question: what does it mean to “design”? Before design was a noun, it was an activity embedded in making. In pre-industrial contexts, the same individual or workshop typically conceived, detailed, and fabricated artifacts—from tools and garments to buildings and ships.",
